description:
In Gethsemane, at the foot of the Mount of Olives, Jesus agonised with the immense physical, emotional, and spiritual battle before Him - whether to go through with Calvary or not. Should he suffer eternal separation from his father due to the sins of humanity? Or should he leave mankind to their own peril and return to heaven? It was in Gethsemane that he said, not my will but thine be done and the decision was made to go through with the plan of salvation, as painful as it would be for Jesus. Today we can have eternal life because of the decision made in this humble garden.
